    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-basa-with-curry-sauce-and-green-bean-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, add the <strong>chopped\u00a0green beans</strong>, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, add a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>green bean rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-basa-with-curry-sauce-and-green-bean-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong> to a bowl and mix together with your <strong>ground\u00a0turmeric</strong> and <strong>curry powder</strong>, then season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>\u00a0\u2013 this is your <strong>curry butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-basa-with-curry-sauce-and-green-bean-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Chop your<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> of the<strong> curry butter\u00a0</strong>(save the rest for later!) over a medium-high heat</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-basa-with-curry-sauce-and-green-bean-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once melted, add your <strong>smoked basa fillet[s] </strong>and\u00a0cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through</p><p>Once done, transfer to a plate, set aside and reserve the pan \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-basa-with-curry-sauce-and-green-bean-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> halved\u00a0cherry tomatoes</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>cold\u00a0water </strong>to the reserved pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for\u00a04 min or until the tomatoes start to soften</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-basa-with-curry-sauce-and-green-bean-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>remaining curry butter</strong> and your <strong>clotted cream</strong> to\u00a0the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt\u00a0</strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 2 min further or until the sauce\u00a0has thickened slightly\u00a0\u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>curry sauce</strong></p><p>Once thickened, return the <strong>smoky</strong> <strong>basa</strong>\u00a0to the pan and cook for a further 1 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-basa-with-curry-sauce-and-green-bean-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> smoky basa</strong>\u00a0over the <strong>green bean rice</strong></p><p>Pour over any <strong>remaining\u00a0curry sauce </strong>and garnish with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
